I don't think S4 SSW is necessarily stronger than S5 SKT. SSW was so dominant at worlds because they were a strong early-mid game team playing in a snowbally map-play based meta, hence them showing their dominance through strong snowballs and short average game times. SKT is a strong laning/skirmishing team playing in a much more controlled and objective-based meta, and they've showed their dominance through that outlet just as well (getting to the finals without dropping a single inhib, consistently closing even games in 3 mins after getting a single lead, only struggling in 2-3 games the whole tournament just like SSW, 14-0 streak, etc).  Personally I don't think the two can be compared, as they both brought the absolute peak dominating play of LoL in their respective metas. You can't really say SSW was more dominant because they were better at snowballing and had shorter game times, for the same reason you can't say SKT was more dominant because they were better around controlling and snowballing off objectives. If the two were to play in S4, SSW would probably snowball SKT, whereas if they played in S5 SKT would choke them out of the map. In that sense they were equal in their dominance IMO.
